* Drawing a diagram helps, even if you don't have specific coordinates.
* Remember your tools:
* Ratio Theorem
* Comparing Coefficients
* Parallel if and only if ka=b
* \(a\)\(\bullet\)\(b=|a||b|cos\theta\), \(a\)\(\times\)\(b=|a||b|sin\theta\)\(\overbrace{(n)}\)
* Be ready to use a combination of these tools.
* Remember properties of dot/cross product. (\(\alpha\)\(\times\)\(b\)\(=\)\(-\)\(b\)\(\times\)\(a\), \(2\alpha\)\(\times\)\(b\)\(=\)\(\alpha\)\(\times\)\(2b\), distributiveness, etc.)
