And thus they are collinear, as required.

A quicker method: Notice that \(OC\) is exactly the vector that divides AB into the ratio \(\lambda\): \(\mu\), by the ratio theorem. And if it divides the line segment AB, it must lie on AB. Hence A,B,C are collinear.

